   During the progress of the case the prisoners withdrew their pleas, and Townsend 
   PLEADED GUILTY 
   to the Second and Ninth Counts (conspiring to obtain credit by false pretences and other frauds, and obtaining credit, being an undischarged bankrupt);

 and 

      Longhurst to the First and Third Counts (obtaining credit by false pretences and other frauds
).

The JURY recommended Brinsmead and Jordan to mercy. BRINS
MEAD—
Six Months' Hard Labour;
BALLANTINE—
Three Months' Hard Labour;
